Remove any nails or screws that were leftover from your decorations. Painting over these nails or screws will look tacky and less professional. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/76/Paint-an-Accent-Wall-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Paint-an-Accent-Wall-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/76/Paint-an-Accent-Wall-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Paint-an-Accent-Wall-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
